stylometry:
The variables that must be considered when setting the level of safety stock would first be the variable that a company can control.  This variable would be the service level.  The service level is the percentage that the company wants to meet of demand.  

The other variabels that need to be considered, but are unpredictable, would be EDDLT and it's variance, as well as Lead Time and it's variance.  Lead time is the time of service compared to the actual time of arrival.  EDDLT and Lead time are things that are unpredictable because a company cannot determine them.  This is why they need to be considered strongly because saftety stock is essentially the back-up plan. It is the back-up inventory that can be used when everything else is gone, it could be considered the buffer.

It's important to take all of these variable into consideration in order to set a prime and ideal level of safety stock.
